## Task: cloche status (no run ID) should show daemon status overview

When `cloche status` is invoked with no run ID, it should display daemon status information instead of erroring or showing nothing.

## Behavior

Display the following:

- **Version** of the daemon

- **If in a project directory (and --all not specified):**
  - Project name
  - Concurrency setting (e.g. max concurrency)
  - Orchestration loop status (e.g. running or stopped)
  - Successful / total runs (this project only) in the past hour
  - Active runs: [active run count]
    - [run id]: [duration]

- **If not in a project directory or --all specified:**
  - Successful / total runs (total) in the past hour
  - Active runs: [active run count]
    - [run id]: [duration]
